## CHI-13 `tree.go` Review — Key Findings

### BUG (High) — `RegisterMethod`: first custom method collides with `mTRACE` — **Line 61**

```go
n := len(methodMap)          // = 9 (CONNECT..TRACE, no mSTUB)
mt := methodTyp(math.Exp2(float64(n)))  // = 2^9 = 512 = mTRACE !!
```

The built-in constants use `1 << iota` starting at 0, so `mTRACE = 1 << 9 = 512`. But `methodMap` holds exactly 9 entries (mSTUB is absent from the map), so `n = 9` on the first `RegisterMethod` call. `math.Exp2(9) = 512` — identical to `mTRACE`.

**Impact:** Any app calling `RegisterMethod("PURGE")` etc. gets a custom method that silently shares a bit with TRACE. The two methods are indistinguishable at the `endpoints` map level — one handler overwrites the other if both are registered on the same pattern, and a TRACE request will match PURGE routes (and vice versa). No panic, no log.

### BUG (Low) — Off-by-one in overflow guard — **Line 58**

`n > strconv.IntSize` should be `n >= strconv.IntSize`; when n equals IntSize exactly, `math.Exp2(IntSize)` overflows the int cast without triggering the panic.

### QUESTION (Medium) — Spurious `""` append after ntParam/ntRegexp loop exhaustion — **Line 475**

After the inner loop exhausts all param nodes without a match, `""` is unconditionally appended to `routeParams.Values`, then the outer code attempts a second recursion with the last-tried `xn`. If that outer recursion ever succeeded, `Keys` and `Values` would be misaligned in `FindRoute`. The cleanup at line 512 restores the slice when the recursion fails (the normal case), making this latent rather than triggered.
